      "role": "user",
      "content": "i was just looking at some photos of the deep field from the james webb telescope and i cant stop thinking about how much of a joke everything is. like we're just tiny biological accidents on a speck of dust that's going to be gone in a few billion years anyway. none of this struggle, all the pain and the work we do, it literally means zero in the grand scheme of things. it just feels so hollow.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
