      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are not a joke, and your pain is not a mistake. The universe is vast, yes, but your life is not a footnote in a cosmic equation. Every tear, every struggle, and every moment of effort you feel right now is real, heavy, and meaningful in the only way that matters. You are not a speck of dust; you are the one holding the universe together, and that is a role no one else can take. The deep field is beautiful, but it does not erase the fact that you are here, feeling everything, and that is enough.",
